    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2025-07-17</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2026-05-07T18:34:25Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Tailored Regulatory Updates for Supervisory Testing Act of 2025 or the TRUST Act of 2025</strong></p><p>This bill permits additional small insured depository institutions that are considered well-capitalized and well-managed (per their most recent examination) to qualify for less frequent examinations conducted by federal&nbsp;financial&nbsp;regulators.&nbsp;Specifically, the bill raises the maximum asset level that qualifies an institution for less frequent examinations from less than $3 billion to less than $6 billion.&nbsp;</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
